  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Peel and chop the <strong>potatoes</strong> into rough, bite-sized pieces</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>potatoes</strong> to a pot of <strong>boiled water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, cook for 12-15 min or until fork-tender, then drain and return to the pot to steam dry</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/853.-step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/853.-step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/853.-step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/853.-step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/853.-step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Reboil a kettle</p><p>Peel and finely chop the<strong> brown onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p><p>Top, tail, peel and finely dice the <strong>carrots</strong></p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of<strong> olive oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>chopped onion</strong> and <strong>diced carrots</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 5-8 min or until softened slightly</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/853.-step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/853.-step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/853.-step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/853.-step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/853.-step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the onion and carrots are softening, peel and finely chop (or grate) the<strong> garlic</strong></p><p>Chop the <strong>chestnut mushrooms</strong> into quarters (or rip them up with your hands to save time)</p><p>Strip the<strong> thyme leaves</strong> from their stalks, discard the stalks</p><p>Tip: Hold the top of the herb sprigs firmly and slide your fingers down their lengths to easily remove the leaves</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/853.-step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/853.-step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/853.-step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/853.-step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/853.-step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once softened, add the<strong> chopped mushrooms</strong>,<strong> half </strong>of the<strong> chopped garlic</strong> (save the rest for later!) and the<strong> thyme leaves</strong> to the pan</p><p>Reduce the heat to medium and cook for 2 min</p><p>Meanwhile, drain and rinse the<strong> green lentils</strong></p><p>Dissolve the <strong>vegetable stock mix</strong>,<strong> tomato paste</strong> and <strong>Henderson's Relish</strong> in 250ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[500ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong> – this is your <strong>tomato stock</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/853.-step-4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
